											<span id="DataList1__ctl1_Label1"><font face="Verdana" size="1"><P>I`ve been working on the items component and have the new code about 70% done.&nbsp; When it`s deployed, you will be able to do raid loot purchases/awardings via a search button which querys an item database, sending back the item name and stats.&nbsp; This will be a big time saver for you since you wont have to maintain your own `Item List`.&nbsp; I will leave the feature in, for custom things likes like plat awardings etc.&nbsp;&nbsp; For the most part though, you should use the new item database instead of going through the trouble of adding all your own items.&nbsp;&nbsp; The database should be current up to and including LDoN.&nbsp; </P>
<P>You will also be able to use this new database to show stats on items that dropped on your raid.&nbsp; I am going to program up a component that will create the images of the stats `on the fly` so you can search the item, get the link and use that link on your news page, for example, to show the item(s).&nbsp; As with all other images, you will not be able to hotlink it to another server though.</P>
<P>I will probably be done everything in the next couple days, depending on work.</P></font></span>
