											<span id="DataList1__ctl3_Label1"><font face="Verdana" size="1"><P>The raid dump feature that was recently added to the Raid Management console, which right now is broken, will be added to the Raid insertion page.&nbsp; I am going to continue support for the present method of insertion (the fugly /who list), but I encourage everyone to use the raid dump feature instead.</P>
<P>Up until the dump feature was added in EQ, the who list (or raid channel dumps etc) was the only way to parse who was on the raid.&nbsp; This new feature will create a text file of everyone on the raid, their group #, and the group leaders.&nbsp; Only the name will be parsed.</P>
<P>I have the component finished, I just have to write the database parameters to handle the new component.&nbsp; So look for another message later today, tommorow at the latest.</P></font></span>
										</td>
