											<span id="DataList1__ctl5_Label1"><font face="Verdana" size="1"><P>I added a column on the Roster so players can put their total AA points.&nbsp; You can, of course, hide this column if you don`t want it by clicking the `Configure View` link on the roster (when you are logged in as an Administrator).&nbsp; You can edit this column by going into edit mode, and the player can edit it in their profile editor.</P>
<P>There was a bug in the roster edit that prevented you from editing it if you had columns hidden to everyone, including Admins.&nbsp; Prior to the fix you had to have the visibility to be set to atleast Admins to see it, so that you could edit.&nbsp; This has been fixed.</P>
<P>I looked around at methods that I might have forgotten to re-fill the cache after updates.&nbsp; This caused the roster, for example, to not show the correct number of raids or points when an admin would update it.&nbsp; I found a few, and fixed it.. there are probably more, I will find the rest and fix em.</P></font></span>
										</td>
	</tr><tr>
		<td>
											<TABLE style="HEIGHT: 21px" borderColor="#b0c4de" cellSpacing="0" borderColorDark="#b0c4de"
												cellPadding="0" width="100%" borderColorLight="#b0c4de" border="0">
												<TR>
													<TD borderColor="#b0c4de" borderColorLight="#b0c4de" width="50%" bgColor="gray" borderColorDark="#b0c4de">
														<span id="DataList1__ctl6_Label2"><b><font face="Verdana" color="Maroon" size="1">Raid List sortable, fixed Gif image bug</font></b></span></TD>
													<TD borderColor="#b0c4de" borderColorLight="#b0c4de" align="right" bgColor="gray" borderColorDark="#b0c4de">
														<span id="DataList1__ctl6_Label3"><b><font face="Verdana" color="Maroon" size="1">Tuesday, October 14, 2003 - 2:08:45 PM</font></b></span></TD>
												</TR>
											</TABLE>
											<span id="DataList1__ctl6_Label1"><font face="Verdana" size="1"><P>I added full sorting to the raid list.&nbsp; You can now sort by name, date, participants etc.&nbsp; If you click the same column twice, you can sort ascending or descending.&nbsp; I can`t believe I didn`t do this before, it just kept getting forgotten I guess.</P>
<P>There was a bug in my graphics handling engine, which caused Gif images to get converted to jpeg images.&nbsp; It wasn`t a big deal, unless the gif was animated, or had transparent backgrounds.&nbsp; This is now fixed, and my engine will output gifs as gifs.&nbsp; This engine is the one that checks to make sure nobody is hot-linking pictures to the server.&nbsp; </P>
<P>I also increased the timeout timer for logins.&nbsp; So if you are logged in and editing your news or whever, it won`t make you login if you spend more than 30minutes of inactivity (typing etc).&nbsp; It now gives you 60 minutes.</P>
<P>I am probably going to implement an items database in the next patch.&nbsp; This will allow you to pick items from a centralized list with proper stats/graphics and simply assign your value to the item upon purchase.&nbsp; I have to implement it so its backwards compatible with the existing system, hopefully it won`t be&nbsp;a big deal :)</P>
<P>Also, the new raid dump feature of the Guild Manager in EQ will be coded in.. i just need someone to email me a sample of the dump so I can code up my parser to accept it.&nbsp; Ironically, I am not in a guild, and don`t have access to a sample file right now.&nbsp; So if someone can email me with a sample file, that would be great!</P></font></span>
										</td>
	</tr><tr>
