											</TABLE>
											<span id="DataList1__ctl8_Label1"><font face="Verdana" size="1"><P>I am coding up a module to allow guilds to register their own domains.&nbsp; This will allow your guild to have its address as <A href="http://www.yourguild.com">www.yourguild.com</A> or whatever you want, as long as the name is available.&nbsp; I coded up the handler for custom domains a few weeks ago, and I have a few guilds using it.. it seems to be working well.&nbsp;</P>
<P>&nbsp;I will admit, I wasn`t sure how well it would work... to my knowlege, GuildWizard.com is the only site of it`s kind that can handle custom domains like this.&nbsp; Most services just can`t offer it, because of software/programming limitations.&nbsp; I had implement 3 different methods in order to accomplish it, but it was worth it in the end.&nbsp; I really think it will add a lot more to a guild`s site if the name is personalized.</P>
<P>I will keep the cost for registering custom domains very competitive.&nbsp; Roughly half the cost of what Network Solutions charges, but I have to make sure.</P></font></span>
